39/*
40 * misc hw access wrappers/control functions
41 */
42
43void
44NVWriteVgaSeq(struct drm_device *dev, int head, uint8_t index, uint8_t value)
45{
46 NVWritePRMVIO(dev, head, NV_PRMVIO_SRX, index);
47 NVWritePRMVIO(dev, head, NV_PRMVIO_SR, value);
48}
49
50uint8_t
51NVReadVgaSeq(struct drm_device *dev, int head, uint8_t index)
52{
53 NVWritePRMVIO(dev, head, NV_PRMVIO_SRX, index);
54 return NVReadPRMVIO(dev, head, NV_PRMVIO_SR);
55}
56
57void
58NVWriteVgaGr(struct drm_device *dev, int head, uint8_t index, uint8_t value)
59{
60 NVWritePRMVIO(dev, head, NV_PRMVIO_GRX, index);
61 NVWritePRMVIO(dev, head, NV_PRMVIO_GX, value);
62}
63
64uint8_t
65NVReadVgaGr(struct drm_device *dev, int head, uint8_t index)
66{
67 NVWritePRMVIO(dev, head, NV_PRMVIO_GRX, index);
68 return NVReadPRMVIO(dev, head, NV_PRMVIO_GX);
69}

71/* CR44 takes values 0 (head A), 3 (head B) and 4 (heads tied)
72 * it affects only the 8 bit vga io regs, which we access using mmio at
73 * 0xc{0,2}3c*, 0x60{1,3}3*, and 0x68{1,3}3d*
74 * in general, the set value of cr44 does not matter: reg access works as
75 * expected and values can be set for the appropriate head by using a 0x2000
76 * offset as required
77 * however:
78 * a) pre nv40, the head B range of PRMVIO regs at 0xc23c* was not exposed and
79 * cr44 must be set to 0 or 3 for accessing values on the correct head
80 * through the common 0xc03c* addresses
81 * b) in tied mode (4) head B is programmed to the values set on head A, and
82 * access using the head B addresses can have strange results, ergo we leave
83 * tied mode in init once we know to what cr44 should be restored on exit
84 *
85 * the owner parameter is slightly abused:
86 * 0 and 1 are treated as head values and so the set value is (owner * 3)
87 * other values are treated as literal values to set
88 */
89void
90NVSetOwner(struct drm_device *dev, int owner)
91{
92 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
93
94 if (owner == 1)
95 owner *= 3;
96
97 if (drm->device.info.chipset == 0x11) {
98 /* This might seem stupid, but the blob does it and
99 * omitting it often locks the system up.
100 */
101 NVReadVgaCrtc(dev, 0, NV_CIO_SR_LOCK_INDEX);
102 NVReadVgaCrtc(dev, 1, NV_CIO_SR_LOCK_INDEX);
103 }
104
105 /* CR44 is always changed on CRTC0 */
106 NVWriteVgaCrtc(dev, 0, NV_CIO_CRE_44, owner);
107
108 if (drm->device.info.chipset == 0x11) { /* set me harder */
109 NVWriteVgaCrtc(dev, 0, NV_CIO_CRE_2E, owner);
110 NVWriteVgaCrtc(dev, 0, NV_CIO_CRE_2E, owner);
111 }
112}
113
114void
115NVBlankScreen(struct drm_device *dev, int head, bool blank)
116{
117 unsigned char seq1;
118
119 if (nv_two_heads(dev))
120 NVSetOwner(dev, head);
121
122 seq1 = NVReadVgaSeq(dev, head, NV_VIO_SR_CLOCK_INDEX);
123
124 NVVgaSeqReset(dev, head, true);
125 if (blank)
126 NVWriteVgaSeq(dev, head, NV_VIO_SR_CLOCK_INDEX, seq1 | 0x20);
127 else
128 NVWriteVgaSeq(dev, head, NV_VIO_SR_CLOCK_INDEX, seq1 & ~0x20);
129 NVVgaSeqReset(dev, head, false);
130}

132/*
133 * PLL getting
134 */
135
136static void
137nouveau_hw_decode_pll(struct drm_device *dev, uint32_t reg1, uint32_t pll1,
138 uint32_t pll2, struct nvkm_pll_vals *pllvals)
139{
140 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
141
142 /* to force parsing as single stage (i.e. nv40 vplls) pass pll2 as 0 */
143
144 /* log2P is & 0x7 as never more than 7, and nv30/35 only uses 3 bits */
145 pllvals->log2P = (pll1 >> 16) & 0x7;
146 pllvals->N2 = pllvals->M2 = 1;
147
148 if (reg1 <= 0x405c) {
149 pllvals->NM1 = pll2 & 0xffff;
150 /* single stage NVPLL and VPLLs use 1 << 8, MPLL uses 1 << 12 */
151 if (!(pll1 & 0x1100))
152 pllvals->NM2 = pll2 >> 16;
153 } else {
154 pllvals->NM1 = pll1 & 0xffff;
155 if (nv_two_reg_pll(dev) && pll2 & NV31_RAMDAC_ENABLE_VCO2)
156 pllvals->NM2 = pll2 & 0xffff;
157 else if (drm->device.info.chipset == 0x30 || drm->device.info.chipset == 0x35) {
158 pllvals->M1 &= 0xf; /* only 4 bits */
159 if (pll1 & NV30_RAMDAC_ENABLE_VCO2) {
160 pllvals->M2 = (pll1 >> 4) & 0x7;
161 pllvals->N2 = ((pll1 >> 21) & 0x18) |
162 ((pll1 >> 19) & 0x7);
163 }
164 }
165 }
166}
167
168int
169nouveau_hw_get_pllvals(struct drm_device *dev, enum nvbios_pll_type plltype,
170 struct nvkm_pll_vals *pllvals)
171{
172 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
173 struct nvif_object *device = &drm->device.object;
174 struct nvkm_bios *bios = nvxx_bios(&drm->device);
175 uint32_t reg1, pll1, pll2 = 0;
176 struct nvbios_pll pll_lim;
177 int ret;
178
179 ret = nvbios_pll_parse(bios, plltype, &pll_lim);
180 if (ret || !(reg1 = pll_lim.reg))
181 return -ENOENT;
182
183 pll1 = nvif_rd32(device, reg1);
184 if (reg1 <= 0x405c)
185 pll2 = nvif_rd32(device, reg1 + 4);
186 else if (nv_two_reg_pll(dev)) {
187 uint32_t reg2 = reg1 + (reg1 == NV_RAMDAC_VPLL2 ? 0x5c : 0x70);
188
189 pll2 = nvif_rd32(device, reg2);
190 }
191
192 if (drm->device.info.family == NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_CELSIUS && reg1 >= NV_PRAMDAC_VPLL_COEFF) {
193 uint32_t ramdac580 = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_580);
194
195 /* check whether vpll has been forced into single stage mode */
196 if (reg1 == NV_PRAMDAC_VPLL_COEFF) {
197 if (ramdac580 & NV_RAMDAC_580_VPLL1_ACTIVE)
198 pll2 = 0;
199 } else
200 if (ramdac580 & NV_RAMDAC_580_VPLL2_ACTIVE)
201 pll2 = 0;
202 }
203
204 nouveau_hw_decode_pll(dev, reg1, pll1, pll2, pllvals);
205 pllvals->refclk = pll_lim.refclk;
206 return 0;
207}
208
209int
210nouveau_hw_pllvals_to_clk(struct nvkm_pll_vals *pv)
211{
212 /* Avoid divide by zero if called at an inappropriate time */
213 if (!pv->M1 || !pv->M2)
214 return 0;
215
216 return pv->N1 * pv->N2 * pv->refclk / (pv->M1 * pv->M2) >> pv->log2P;
217}
218
219int
220nouveau_hw_get_clock(struct drm_device *dev, enum nvbios_pll_type plltype)
221{
222 struct nvkm_pll_vals pllvals;
223 int ret;
224
225 if (plltype == PLL_MEMORY &&
226 (dev->pdev->device & 0x0ff0) == CHIPSET_NFORCE) {
227 uint32_t mpllP;
228
229 pci_read_config_dword(pci_get_bus_and_slot(0, 3), 0x6c, &mpllP);
230 mpllP = (mpllP >> 8) & 0xf;
231 if (!mpllP)
232 mpllP = 4;
233
234 return 400000 / mpllP;
235 } else
236 if (plltype == PLL_MEMORY &&
237 (dev->pdev->device & 0xff0) == CHIPSET_NFORCE2) {
238 uint32_t clock;
239
240 pci_read_config_dword(pci_get_bus_and_slot(0, 5), 0x4c, &clock);
241 return clock / 1000;
242 }
243
244 ret = nouveau_hw_get_pllvals(dev, plltype, &pllvals);
245 if (ret)
246 return ret;
247
248 return nouveau_hw_pllvals_to_clk(&pllvals);
249}
250
251static void
252nouveau_hw_fix_bad_vpll(struct drm_device *dev, int head)
253{
254 /* the vpll on an unused head can come up with a random value, way
255 * beyond the pll limits. for some reason this causes the chip to
256 * lock up when reading the dac palette regs, so set a valid pll here
257 * when such a condition detected. only seen on nv11 to date
258 */
259
260 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
261 struct nvif_device *device = &drm->device;
262 struct nvkm_clk *clk = nvxx_clk(device);
263 struct nvkm_bios *bios = nvxx_bios(device);
264 struct nvbios_pll pll_lim;
265 struct nvkm_pll_vals pv;
266 enum nvbios_pll_type pll = head ? PLL_VPLL1 : PLL_VPLL0;
267
268 if (nvbios_pll_parse(bios, pll, &pll_lim))
269 return;
270 nouveau_hw_get_pllvals(dev, pll, &pv);
271
272 if (pv.M1 >= pll_lim.vco1.min_m && pv.M1 <= pll_lim.vco1.max_m &&
273 pv.N1 >= pll_lim.vco1.min_n && pv.N1 <= pll_lim.vco1.max_n &&
274 pv.log2P <= pll_lim.max_p)
275 return;
276
277 NV_WARN(drm, "VPLL %d outwith limits, attempting to fix\n", head + 1);
278
279 /* set lowest clock within static limits */
280 pv.M1 = pll_lim.vco1.max_m;
281 pv.N1 = pll_lim.vco1.min_n;
282 pv.log2P = pll_lim.max_p_usable;
283 clk->pll_prog(clk, pll_lim.reg, &pv);
284}

286/*
287 * vga font save/restore
288 */
289
290static void nouveau_vga_font_io(struct drm_device *dev,
291#ifdef __NetBSD__
292 bus_space_tag_t iovramt,
293 bus_space_handle_t iovramh,
294#else
295 void __iomem *iovram,
296#endif
297 bool save, unsigned plane)
298{
299 unsigned i;
300
301 NVWriteVgaSeq(dev, 0, NV_VIO_SR_PLANE_MASK_INDEX, 1 << plane);
302 NVWriteVgaGr(dev, 0, NV_VIO_GX_READ_MAP_INDEX, plane);
303 for (i = 0; i < 16384; i++) {
304 if (save) {
305#ifdef __NetBSD__
306 nv04_display(dev)->saved_vga_font[plane][i] =
307 bus_space_read_stream_4(iovramt, iovramh, i * 4);
308#else
309 nv04_display(dev)->saved_vga_font[plane][i] =
310 ioread32_native(iovram + i * 4);
311#endif
312 } else {
313#ifdef __NetBSD__
314 bus_space_write_stream_4(iovramt, iovramh, i * 4,
315 nv04_display(dev)->saved_vga_font[plane][i]);
316#else
317 iowrite32_native(nv04_display(dev)->saved_vga_font[plane][i],
318 iovram + i * 4);
319#endif
320 }
321 }
322}
323
324void
325nouveau_hw_save_vga_fonts(struct drm_device *dev, bool save)
326{
327 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
328 uint8_t misc, gr4, gr5, gr6, seq2, seq4;
329 bool graphicsmode;
330 unsigned plane;
331#ifdef __NetBSD__
332 bus_space_tag_t iovramt;
333 bus_space_handle_t iovramh;
334 bus_size_t iovramsz;
335#else
336 void __iomem *iovram;
337#endif
338
339 if (nv_two_heads(dev))
340 NVSetOwner(dev, 0);
341
342 NVSetEnablePalette(dev, 0, true);
343 graphicsmode = NVReadVgaAttr(dev, 0, NV_CIO_AR_MODE_INDEX) & 1;
344 NVSetEnablePalette(dev, 0, false);
345
346 if (graphicsmode) /* graphics mode => framebuffer => no need to save */
347 return;
348
349 NV_INFO(drm, "%sing VGA fonts\n", save ? "Sav" : "Restor");
350
351 /* map first 64KiB of VRAM, holds VGA fonts etc */
352#ifdef __NetBSD__
353 if (pci_mapreg_map(&dev->pdev->pd_pa, PCI_BAR(1),
354 pci_mapreg_type(dev->pdev->pd_pa.pa_pc,
355 dev->pdev->pd_pa.pa_tag, PCI_BAR(1)),
356 0, &iovramt, &iovramh, NULL, &iovramsz)) {
357 NV_ERROR(drm, "Failed to map VRAM, "
358 "cannot save/restore VGA fonts.\n");
359 return;
360 }
361#else
362 iovram = ioremap(pci_resource_start(dev->pdev, 1), 65536);
363 if (!iovram) {
364 NV_ERROR(drm, "Failed to map VRAM, "
365 "cannot save/restore VGA fonts.\n");
366 return;
367 }
368#endif
369
370 if (nv_two_heads(dev))
371 NVBlankScreen(dev, 1, true);
372 NVBlankScreen(dev, 0, true);
373
374 /* save control regs */
375 misc = NVReadPRMVIO(dev, 0, NV_PRMVIO_MISC__READ);
376 seq2 = NVReadVgaSeq(dev, 0, NV_VIO_SR_PLANE_MASK_INDEX);
377 seq4 = NVReadVgaSeq(dev, 0, NV_VIO_SR_MEM_MODE_INDEX);
378 gr4 = NVReadVgaGr(dev, 0, NV_VIO_GX_READ_MAP_INDEX);
379 gr5 = NVReadVgaGr(dev, 0, NV_VIO_GX_MODE_INDEX);
380 gr6 = NVReadVgaGr(dev, 0, NV_VIO_GX_MISC_INDEX);
381
382 NVWritePRMVIO(dev, 0, NV_PRMVIO_MISC__WRITE, 0x67);
383 NVWriteVgaSeq(dev, 0, NV_VIO_SR_MEM_MODE_INDEX, 0x6);
384 NVWriteVgaGr(dev, 0, NV_VIO_GX_MODE_INDEX, 0x0);
385 NVWriteVgaGr(dev, 0, NV_VIO_GX_MISC_INDEX, 0x5);
386
387 /* store font in planes 0..3 */
388 for (plane = 0; plane < 4; plane++)
389#ifdef __NetBSD__
390 nouveau_vga_font_io(dev, iovramt, iovramh, save, plane);
391#else
392 nouveau_vga_font_io(dev, iovram, save, plane);
393#endif
394
395 /* restore control regs */
396 NVWritePRMVIO(dev, 0, NV_PRMVIO_MISC__WRITE, misc);
397 NVWriteVgaGr(dev, 0, NV_VIO_GX_READ_MAP_INDEX, gr4);
398 NVWriteVgaGr(dev, 0, NV_VIO_GX_MODE_INDEX, gr5);
399 NVWriteVgaGr(dev, 0, NV_VIO_GX_MISC_INDEX, gr6);
400 NVWriteVgaSeq(dev, 0, NV_VIO_SR_PLANE_MASK_INDEX, seq2);
401 NVWriteVgaSeq(dev, 0, NV_VIO_SR_MEM_MODE_INDEX, seq4);
402
403 if (nv_two_heads(dev))
404 NVBlankScreen(dev, 1, false);
405 NVBlankScreen(dev, 0, false);
406
407#ifdef __NetBSD__
408 bus_space_unmap(iovramt, iovramh, iovramsz);
409#else
410 iounmap(iovram);
411#endif
412}

418static void
419rd_cio_state(struct drm_device *dev, int head,
420 struct nv04_crtc_reg *crtcstate, int index)
421{
422 crtcstate->CRTC[index] = NVReadVgaCrtc(dev, head, index);
423}
424
425static void
426wr_cio_state(struct drm_device *dev, int head,
427 struct nv04_crtc_reg *crtcstate, int index)
428{
429 NVWriteVgaCrtc(dev, head, index, crtcstate->CRTC[index]);
430}
431
432static void
433nv_save_state_ramdac(struct drm_device *dev, int head,
434 struct nv04_mode_state *state)
435{
436 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
437 struct nv04_crtc_reg *regp = &state->crtc_reg[head];
438 int i;
439
440 if (drm->device.info.family >= NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_CELSIUS)
441 regp->nv10_cursync = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_RAMDAC_NV10_CURSYNC);
442
443 nouveau_hw_get_pllvals(dev, head ? PLL_VPLL1 : PLL_VPLL0, &regp->pllvals);
444 state->pllsel = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_PLL_COEFF_SELECT);
445 if (nv_two_heads(dev))
446 state->sel_clk = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_SEL_CLK);
447 if (drm->device.info.chipset == 0x11)
448 regp->dither = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_RAMDAC_DITHER_NV11);
449
450 regp->ramdac_gen_ctrl = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_GENERAL_CONTROL);
451
452 if (nv_gf4_disp_arch(dev))
453 regp->ramdac_630 = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_630);
454 if (drm->device.info.chipset >= 0x30)
455 regp->ramdac_634 = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_634);
456
457 regp->tv_setup = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TV_SETUP);
458 regp->tv_vtotal = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TV_VTOTAL);
459 regp->tv_vskew = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TV_VSKEW);
460 regp->tv_vsync_delay = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TV_VSYNC_DELAY);
461 regp->tv_htotal = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TV_HTOTAL);
462 regp->tv_hskew = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TV_HSKEW);
463 regp->tv_hsync_delay = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TV_HSYNC_DELAY);
464 regp->tv_hsync_delay2 = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TV_HSYNC_DELAY2);
465
466 for (i = 0; i < 7; i++) {
467 uint32_t ramdac_reg = NV_PRAMDAC_FP_VDISPLAY_END + (i * 4);
468 regp->fp_vert_regs[i] = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, ramdac_reg);
469 regp->fp_horiz_regs[i] = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, ramdac_reg + 0x20);
470 }
471
472 if (nv_gf4_disp_arch(dev)) {
473 regp->dither = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_RAMDAC_FP_DITHER);
474 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
475 regp->dither_regs[i] = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_850 + i * 4);
476 regp->dither_regs[i + 3] = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_85C + i * 4);
477 }
478 }
479
480 regp->fp_control = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_FP_TG_CONTROL);
481 regp->fp_debug_0 = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_FP_DEBUG_0);
482 if (!nv_gf4_disp_arch(dev) && head == 0) {
483 /* early chips don't allow access to PRAMDAC_TMDS_* without
484 * the head A FPCLK on (nv11 even locks up) */
485 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_FP_DEBUG_0, regp->fp_debug_0 &
486 ~NV_PRAMDAC_FP_DEBUG_0_PWRDOWN_FPCLK);
487 }
488 regp->fp_debug_1 = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_FP_DEBUG_1);
489 regp->fp_debug_2 = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_FP_DEBUG_2);
490
491 regp->fp_margin_color = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_FP_MARGIN_COLOR);
492
493 if (nv_gf4_disp_arch(dev))
494 regp->ramdac_8c0 = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_8C0);
495
496 if (drm->device.info.family == NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_CURIE) {
497 regp->ramdac_a20 = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_A20);
498 regp->ramdac_a24 = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_A24);
499 regp->ramdac_a34 = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_A34);
500
501 for (i = 0; i < 38; i++)
502 regp->ctv_regs[i] = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head,
503 NV_PRAMDAC_CTV + 4*i);
504 }
505}
506
507static void
508nv_load_state_ramdac(struct drm_device *dev, int head,
509 struct nv04_mode_state *state)
510{
511 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
512 struct nvkm_clk *clk = nvxx_clk(&drm->device);
513 struct nv04_crtc_reg *regp = &state->crtc_reg[head];
514 uint32_t pllreg = head ? NV_RAMDAC_VPLL2 : NV_PRAMDAC_VPLL_COEFF;
515 int i;
516
517 if (drm->device.info.family >= NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_CELSIUS)
518 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_RAMDAC_NV10_CURSYNC, regp->nv10_cursync);
519
520 clk->pll_prog(clk, pllreg, &regp->pllvals);
521 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_PLL_COEFF_SELECT, state->pllsel);
522 if (nv_two_heads(dev))
523 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, 0, NV_PRAMDAC_SEL_CLK, state->sel_clk);
524 if (drm->device.info.chipset == 0x11)
525 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_RAMDAC_DITHER_NV11, regp->dither);
526
527 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_GENERAL_CONTROL, regp->ramdac_gen_ctrl);
528
529 if (nv_gf4_disp_arch(dev))
530 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_630, regp->ramdac_630);
531 if (drm->device.info.chipset >= 0x30)
532 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_634, regp->ramdac_634);
533
534 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TV_SETUP, regp->tv_setup);
535 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TV_VTOTAL, regp->tv_vtotal);
536 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TV_VSKEW, regp->tv_vskew);
537 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TV_VSYNC_DELAY, regp->tv_vsync_delay);
538 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TV_HTOTAL, regp->tv_htotal);
539 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TV_HSKEW, regp->tv_hskew);
540 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TV_HSYNC_DELAY, regp->tv_hsync_delay);
541 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_TV_HSYNC_DELAY2, regp->tv_hsync_delay2);
542
543 for (i = 0; i < 7; i++) {
544 uint32_t ramdac_reg = NV_PRAMDAC_FP_VDISPLAY_END + (i * 4);
545
546 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, ramdac_reg, regp->fp_vert_regs[i]);
547 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, ramdac_reg + 0x20, regp->fp_horiz_regs[i]);
548 }
549
550 if (nv_gf4_disp_arch(dev)) {
551 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_RAMDAC_FP_DITHER, regp->dither);
552 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
553 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_850 + i * 4, regp->dither_regs[i]);
554 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_85C + i * 4, regp->dither_regs[i + 3]);
555 }
556 }
557
558 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_FP_TG_CONTROL, regp->fp_control);
559 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_FP_DEBUG_0, regp->fp_debug_0);
560 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_FP_DEBUG_1, regp->fp_debug_1);
561 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_FP_DEBUG_2, regp->fp_debug_2);
562
563 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_FP_MARGIN_COLOR, regp->fp_margin_color);
564
565 if (nv_gf4_disp_arch(dev))
566 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_8C0, regp->ramdac_8c0);
567
568 if (drm->device.info.family == NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_CURIE) {
569 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_A20, regp->ramdac_a20);
570 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_A24, regp->ramdac_a24);
571 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_A34, regp->ramdac_a34);
572
573 for (i = 0; i < 38; i++)
574 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head,
575 NV_PRAMDAC_CTV + 4*i, regp->ctv_regs[i]);
576 }
577}
578
579static void
580nv_save_state_vga(struct drm_device *dev, int head,
581 struct nv04_mode_state *state)
582{
583 struct nv04_crtc_reg *regp = &state->crtc_reg[head];
584 int i;
585
586 regp->MiscOutReg = NVReadPRMVIO(dev, head, NV_PRMVIO_MISC__READ);
587
588 for (i = 0; i < 25; i++)
589 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, i);
590
591 NVSetEnablePalette(dev, head, true);
592 for (i = 0; i < 21; i++)
593 regp->Attribute[i] = NVReadVgaAttr(dev, head, i);
594 NVSetEnablePalette(dev, head, false);
595
596 for (i = 0; i < 9; i++)
597 regp->Graphics[i] = NVReadVgaGr(dev, head, i);
598
599 for (i = 0; i < 5; i++)
600 regp->Sequencer[i] = NVReadVgaSeq(dev, head, i);
601}
602
603static void
604nv_load_state_vga(struct drm_device *dev, int head,
605 struct nv04_mode_state *state)
606{
607 struct nv04_crtc_reg *regp = &state->crtc_reg[head];
608 int i;
609
610 NVWritePRMVIO(dev, head, NV_PRMVIO_MISC__WRITE, regp->MiscOutReg);
611
612 for (i = 0; i < 5; i++)
613 NVWriteVgaSeq(dev, head, i, regp->Sequencer[i]);
614
615 nv_lock_vga_crtc_base(dev, head, false);
616 for (i = 0; i < 25; i++)
617 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, i);
618 nv_lock_vga_crtc_base(dev, head, true);
619
620 for (i = 0; i < 9; i++)
621 NVWriteVgaGr(dev, head, i, regp->Graphics[i]);
622
623 NVSetEnablePalette(dev, head, true);
624 for (i = 0; i < 21; i++)
625 NVWriteVgaAttr(dev, head, i, regp->Attribute[i]);
626 NVSetEnablePalette(dev, head, false);
627}

629static void
630nv_save_state_ext(struct drm_device *dev, int head,
631 struct nv04_mode_state *state)
632{
633 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
634 struct nv04_crtc_reg *regp = &state->crtc_reg[head];
635 int i;
636
637 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_LCD__INDEX);
638 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_RPC0_INDEX);
639 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_RPC1_INDEX);
640 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_LSR_INDEX);
641 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_PIXEL_INDEX);
642 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_HEB__INDEX);
643 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_ENH_INDEX);
644
645 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_FF_INDEX);
646 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_FFLWM__INDEX);
647 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_21);
648
649 if (drm->device.info.family >= NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_KELVIN)
650 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_47);
651
652 if (drm->device.info.family >= NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_RANKINE)
653 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, 0x9f);
654
655 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_49);
656 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_HCUR_ADDR0_INDEX);
657 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_HCUR_ADDR1_INDEX);
658 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_HCUR_ADDR2_INDEX);
659 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_ILACE__INDEX);
660
661 if (drm->device.info.family >= NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_CELSIUS) {
662 regp->crtc_830 = NVReadCRTC(dev, head, NV_PCRTC_830);
663 regp->crtc_834 = NVReadCRTC(dev, head, NV_PCRTC_834);
664
665 if (drm->device.info.family >= NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_RANKINE)
666 regp->gpio_ext = NVReadCRTC(dev, head, NV_PCRTC_GPIO_EXT);
667
668 if (drm->device.info.family == NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_CURIE)
669 regp->crtc_850 = NVReadCRTC(dev, head, NV_PCRTC_850);
670
671 if (nv_two_heads(dev))
672 regp->crtc_eng_ctrl = NVReadCRTC(dev, head, NV_PCRTC_ENGINE_CTRL);
673 regp->cursor_cfg = NVReadCRTC(dev, head, NV_PCRTC_CURSOR_CONFIG);
674 }
675
676 regp->crtc_cfg = NVReadCRTC(dev, head, NV_PCRTC_CONFIG);
677
678 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_SCRATCH3__INDEX);
679 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_SCRATCH4__INDEX);
680 if (drm->device.info.family >= NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_CELSIUS) {
681 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_EBR_INDEX);
682 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_CSB);
683 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_4B);
684 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_TVOUT_LATENCY);
685 }
686 /* NV11 and NV20 don't have this, they stop at 0x52. */
687 if (nv_gf4_disp_arch(dev)) {
688 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_42);
689 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_53);
690 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_54);
691
692 for (i = 0; i < 0x10; i++)
693 regp->CR58[i] = NVReadVgaCrtc5758(dev, head, i);
694 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_59);
695 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_5B);
696
697 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_85);
698 rd_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_86);
699 }
700
701 regp->fb_start = NVReadCRTC(dev, head, NV_PCRTC_START);
702}
703
704static void
705nv_load_state_ext(struct drm_device *dev, int head,
706 struct nv04_mode_state *state)
707{
708 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
709 struct nvif_object *device = &drm->device.object;
710 struct nv04_crtc_reg *regp = &state->crtc_reg[head];
711 uint32_t reg900;
712 int i;
713
714 if (drm->device.info.family >= NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_CELSIUS) {
715 if (nv_two_heads(dev))
716 /* setting ENGINE_CTRL (EC) *must* come before
717 * CIO_CRE_LCD, as writing CRE_LCD sets bits 16 & 17 in
718 * EC that should not be overwritten by writing stale EC
719 */
720 NVWriteCRTC(dev, head, NV_PCRTC_ENGINE_CTRL, regp->crtc_eng_ctrl);
721
722 nvif_wr32(device, NV_PVIDEO_STOP, 1);
723 nvif_wr32(device, NV_PVIDEO_INTR_EN, 0);
724 nvif_wr32(device, NV_PVIDEO_OFFSET_BUFF(0), 0);
725 nvif_wr32(device, NV_PVIDEO_OFFSET_BUFF(1), 0);
726 nvif_wr32(device, NV_PVIDEO_LIMIT(0), drm->device.info.ram_size - 1);
727 nvif_wr32(device, NV_PVIDEO_LIMIT(1), drm->device.info.ram_size - 1);
728 nvif_wr32(device, NV_PVIDEO_UVPLANE_LIMIT(0), drm->device.info.ram_size - 1);
729 nvif_wr32(device, NV_PVIDEO_UVPLANE_LIMIT(1), drm->device.info.ram_size - 1);
730 nvif_wr32(device, NV_PBUS_POWERCTRL_2, 0);
731
732 NVWriteCRTC(dev, head, NV_PCRTC_CURSOR_CONFIG, regp->cursor_cfg);
733 NVWriteCRTC(dev, head, NV_PCRTC_830, regp->crtc_830);
734 NVWriteCRTC(dev, head, NV_PCRTC_834, regp->crtc_834);
735
736 if (drm->device.info.family >= NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_RANKINE)
737 NVWriteCRTC(dev, head, NV_PCRTC_GPIO_EXT, regp->gpio_ext);
738
739 if (drm->device.info.family == NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_CURIE) {
740 NVWriteCRTC(dev, head, NV_PCRTC_850, regp->crtc_850);
741
742 reg900 = NVReadRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_900);
743 if (regp->crtc_cfg == NV10_PCRTC_CONFIG_START_ADDRESS_HSYNC)
744 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_900, reg900 | 0x10000);
745 else
746 NVWriteRAMDAC(dev, head, NV_PRAMDAC_900, reg900 & ~0x10000);
747 }
748 }
749
750 NVWriteCRTC(dev, head, NV_PCRTC_CONFIG, regp->crtc_cfg);
751
752 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_RPC0_INDEX);
753 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_RPC1_INDEX);
754 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_LSR_INDEX);
755 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_PIXEL_INDEX);
756 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_LCD__INDEX);
757 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_HEB__INDEX);
758 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_ENH_INDEX);
759 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_FF_INDEX);
760 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_FFLWM__INDEX);
761
762 if (drm->device.info.family >= NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_KELVIN)
763 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_47);
764
765 if (drm->device.info.family >= NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_RANKINE)
766 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, 0x9f);
767
768 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_49);
769 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_HCUR_ADDR0_INDEX);
770 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_HCUR_ADDR1_INDEX);
771 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_HCUR_ADDR2_INDEX);
772 if (drm->device.info.family == NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_CURIE)
773 nv_fix_nv40_hw_cursor(dev, head);
774 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_ILACE__INDEX);
775
776 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_SCRATCH3__INDEX);
777 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_SCRATCH4__INDEX);
778 if (drm->device.info.family >= NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_CELSIUS) {
779 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_EBR_INDEX);
780 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_CSB);
781 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_4B);
782 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_TVOUT_LATENCY);
783 }
784 /* NV11 and NV20 stop at 0x52. */
785 if (nv_gf4_disp_arch(dev)) {
786 if (drm->device.info.family < NV_DEVICE_INFO_V0_KELVIN) {
787 /* Not waiting for vertical retrace before modifying
788 CRE_53/CRE_54 causes lockups. */
789 nvif_msec(&drm->device, 650,
790 if ( (nvif_rd32(device, NV_PRMCIO_INP0__COLOR) & 8))
791 break;
792 );
793 nvif_msec(&drm->device, 650,
794 if (!(nvif_rd32(device, NV_PRMCIO_INP0__COLOR) & 8))
795 break;
796 );
797 }
798
799 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_42);
800 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_53);
801 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_54);
802
803 for (i = 0; i < 0x10; i++)
804 NVWriteVgaCrtc5758(dev, head, i, regp->CR58[i]);
805 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_59);
806 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_5B);
807
808 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_85);
809 wr_cio_state(dev, head, regp, NV_CIO_CRE_86);
810 }
811
812 NVWriteCRTC(dev, head, NV_PCRTC_START, regp->fb_start);
813}

815static void
816nv_save_state_palette(struct drm_device *dev, int head,
817 struct nv04_mode_state *state)
818{
819 struct nvif_object *device = &nouveau_drm(dev)->device.object;
820 int head_offset = head * NV_PRMDIO_SIZE, i;
821
822 nvif_wr08(device, NV_PRMDIO_PIXEL_MASK + head_offset,
823 NV_PRMDIO_PIXEL_MASK_MASK);
824 nvif_wr08(device, NV_PRMDIO_READ_MODE_ADDRESS + head_offset, 0x0);
825
826 for (i = 0; i < 768; i++) {
827 state->crtc_reg[head].DAC[i] = nvif_rd08(device,
828 NV_PRMDIO_PALETTE_DATA + head_offset);
829 }
830
831 NVSetEnablePalette(dev, head, false);
832}

834void
835nouveau_hw_load_state_palette(struct drm_device *dev, int head,
836 struct nv04_mode_state *state)
837{
838 struct nvif_object *device = &nouveau_drm(dev)->device.object;
839 int head_offset = head * NV_PRMDIO_SIZE, i;
840
841 nvif_wr08(device, NV_PRMDIO_PIXEL_MASK + head_offset,
842 NV_PRMDIO_PIXEL_MASK_MASK);
843 nvif_wr08(device, NV_PRMDIO_WRITE_MODE_ADDRESS + head_offset, 0x0);
844
845 for (i = 0; i < 768; i++) {
846 nvif_wr08(device, NV_PRMDIO_PALETTE_DATA + head_offset,
847 state->crtc_reg[head].DAC[i]);
848 }
849
850 NVSetEnablePalette(dev, head, false);
851}
852
853void nouveau_hw_save_state(struct drm_device *dev, int head,
854 struct nv04_mode_state *state)
855{
856 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
857
858 if (drm->device.info.chipset == 0x11)
859 /* NB: no attempt is made to restore the bad pll later on */
860 nouveau_hw_fix_bad_vpll(dev, head);
861 nv_save_state_ramdac(dev, head, state);
862 nv_save_state_vga(dev, head, state);
863 nv_save_state_palette(dev, head, state);
864 nv_save_state_ext(dev, head, state);
865}
866
867void nouveau_hw_load_state(struct drm_device *dev, int head,
868 struct nv04_mode_state *state)
869{
870 NVVgaProtect(dev, head, true);
871 nv_load_state_ramdac(dev, head, state);
872 nv_load_state_ext(dev, head, state);
873 nouveau_hw_load_state_palette(dev, head, state);
874 nv_load_state_vga(dev, head, state);
875 NVVgaProtect(dev, head, false);
876}
